Colombian Stocks: Exito, Ecopetrol, Pacific Rubiales, Canacol

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-07-06T20:44:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/colombian-stocks-exito-ecopetrol-pacific-rubiales-canacol.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 2.1 percent to 13,865.99, while the
Colcap Index dropped 2.3 percent to 1,677.40.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombia’s biggest publicly
traded retailer, fell 1.1 percent to 23,720 pesos, the lowest
since Feb. 22. Exito shareholders approved plans to raise as
much as $1.4 billion by selling new shares as part of a plan to
buy a stake in Uruguayan supermarkets from majority shareholder
Casino Guichard-Perrachon SA, according to a regulatory filing.  Oil companies dropped as crude fell after China’s central
bank raised interest rates and Moody’s Investors Service
downgraded Portugal’s credit rating, heightening concern
economic growth will slow and crimp fuel demand.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
fell 2.5 percent, the most since June 15, to 3,760 pesos, a two-
month low.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PREC)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, fell 3.1 percent
to 46,320 pesos, the lowest since September 2010.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based oil
company that operates fields in  South America , fell 4.2 percent
to 1,825 pesos, the lowest since July 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
